de.oaam.model.oaam.functions

Interface Signal

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ModeDependentElementA, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA, VariantDependentElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SignalImpl

    public interface Signal
extends OaamBaseElementA, VariantDependentElementA, ModeDependentElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Signal'. A signal is information that is exchanged unidirectional from one function to another.

    The following features are supported:

    • Source
    • Target
    • Type
    • In Index
    • Out Index
    • Connection Binding
    See Also:
    FunctionsPackage.getSignal()

      • getConnectionBinding

        Connection getConnectionBinding()
        Returns the value of the 'Connection Binding' reference. This references a unique connection if this signal is strictly bound to one a wire i.e. an atomic block of hardware and funtion, e.g a sensor. This is a so called hardware task. If a device is specified. Also the function outputs should be bound to device connectors. Do not specify a device here if this is a freely assignable function.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Connection Binding' reference.
        See Also:
        setConnectionBinding(Connection), FunctionsPackage.getSignal_ConnectionBinding()
